  <title><anchor xml:id="Icinga_integration" />Integration Overview</title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">Introduction</emphasis></para>

  <para>&name-icinga; can be easily integrated in your existing infrastructure. There are several methods of integrating &name-icinga; with
  the management software you're already using and you can monitor almost any type of new or custom hardware, service, or application that
  you might have.</para>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">Integration Points</emphasis></para>

  <para><inlinemediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="../images/integrationoverview.png" format="PNG"></imagedata>
      </imageobject>
    </inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para>To monitor new hardware, services, or applications, check out the docs on:</para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="plugins">Plugins</link></para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="pluginapi">Plugin API</link></para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="passivechecks">Passive Checks</link></para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="eventhandlers">Event Handlers</link></para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <para>To get data into &name-icinga; from external applications, check out the docs on:</para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="passivechecks">Passive Checks</link></para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="extcommands">External Commands</link></para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <para>To send status, performance, or notification information from &name-icinga; to external applications, check out the docs on:</para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="eventhandlers">Event Handlers</link></para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="configmain-ocsp_command">OCSP</link> and <link linkend="configmain-ochp_command">OCHP</link> Commands</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="perfdata">Performance Data</link></para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="notifications">Notifications</link></para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">Integration Examples</emphasis></para>

  <para>The following documents show some examples on how to integrate &name-icinga; with external applications:</para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="int-tcpwrappers">TCP Wrappers</link> (security alerts)</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="int-snmptrap">SNMP Traps</link> (Arcserve backup job status)</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="int-mklivestatus">mklivestatus</link> (interface from &name-icinga; to several addons like <link xlink:href="&url-nagvis;">&name-nagvis;</link> and <link xlink:href="&url-thruk;">&name-thruk;</link>)</para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

